modernize the nation. The folklorists, however, faced a unique challenge – advocating for modern academic methods while upholding folklore as the key to the nation’s salvation. Largely unknown in the West and underappreciated in China, the Modern Folklore Movement failed to achieve its goal of reinvigorating the Chinese nation. But it helped establish a modern discipline, promoting a spirit of academic independence that influences Chinese intellectuals today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFolklore and nationalismzChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aFolklorexPolitical aspectszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aFolklorezChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial movementszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Folklore & Mythology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311141772140uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483840540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774838405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774838405/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-141772-1  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles